This is unlikely to be a CVS problem. It is more likely a VM/Classloader issue. I notice you are using a beta VM. Can you reproduce on a released VM? Also, does the problem persist after a restart?

It works ok with eclipse 3.2rc1 and jre1.5.0_06.
3.2rc1 still goes wrong with jre1.6b80.

thanks,
Peter
Jeff, Are you aware of any class loading issues with OSGI and the Java 1.6 Beta?
This error needs some investigation.  Why was it closed invalid?  I will investigate the error.
I closed it since the VM was not on the supported list. Reopening to assign to runtime.
I cannot reproduce.  Can you provide project that fails for you?  How do you create a project that has the org.eclipse.team.cvs.core.cvsnature nature assigned to it?
You can get a project with the "org.eclipse.team.cvs.core.cvsnature" repository id (it's not really a nature but has it in the name for backwards compatibility) by checking out a project from CVS.
Downgrading severity because this is only occurring on a 1.6 JRE which is not yet a supported platform.
